The answer depends on whether you are justified in using deadly force. If so, then yes, you may use deadly force against a fleeing felon. However, there are some important considerations that must be made before shooting someone who is running away from you. First, it’s important to understand what constitutes justifiable self-defense under Florida law. In order for your actions to be considered legally justified, they must meet certain criteria: 1) You had reason to believe that your life was threatened;
2) There were no other reasonable alternatives available to protect yourself; and
3) Your response was proportional to the threat posed by the attacker. If these conditions aren’t met, then your actions could potentially lead to criminal charges being filed against you. So before taking any action, make sure you have all of the facts straight!
